-- Christie’s Wine Auctions Fetch Total $5.46 Million in Hong Kong
-- B y   G u y   C o l l i n s
-- 2012-09-10T15:49:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-10/christie-s-wine-auctions-fetch-total-5-46-million-in-hong-kong.html
Christie’s International sold a
total HK$42.32 million ($5.46 million) at two wine sales in  Hong
Kong  Sept. 8, with bidding led by vertical collections of
historic vintages of Chateau Mouton-Rothschild, Chateau Lafite-
Rothschild and  Chateau Latour  dating between 1945 and 2008,
according to results on its website.                    The Mouton collection of 66 bottles sold for HK$1.09
million, 64 bottles of Lafite fetched HK$968,000 and a similar-
sized lot of Latour sold for $871,200.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Guy Collins in London at 
